{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:galatians.4",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "galatians",
    "chapterNumber": 4,
    "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4",
    "summary": "Source text for Galatians 4 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:1",
      "text": "As long as the heir is a child, he differeth nothing from a servant, though he be lord of all,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:2",
      "text": "But is under tutors and governors until the time appointed by the father.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:3",
      "text": "So we also, when we were children, were serving under the elements of the world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:4",
      "text": "But when the fulness of the time was come, God sent his Son, made of a woman, made under the law:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:5",
      "text": "That he might redeem them who were under the law: that we might receive the adoption of sons.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:6",
      "text": "And because you are sons, God hath sent the Spirit of his Son into your hearts, crying: Abba, Father.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:7",
      "text": "Therefore, now he is not a servant, but a son. And if a son, an heir also through God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:8",
      "text": "But then indeed, not knowing God, you served them who, by nature, are not gods.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:9",
      "text": "But now, after that you have known God, or rather are known by God: how turn you again to the weak and needy elements which you desire to serve again?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:10",
      "text": "You observe days and months and times, and years.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:11",
      "text": "I am afraid of you, lest perhaps I have laboured in vain among you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:12",
      "text": "Be ye as I, because I also am as you brethren, I beseech you. You have not injured me at all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:13",
      "text": "And you know how, through infirmity of the flesh, I preached the gospel to you heretofore: and your temptation in my flesh",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:14",
      "text": "You despised not, nor rejected: but received me as an angel of God, even as Christ Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:15",
      "text": "Where is then your blessedness? For I bear you witness that, if it could be done, you would have plucked out your own eyes and would have given them to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:16",
      "text": "Am I then become your enemy, because I tell you the truth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:17",
      "text": "They are zealous in your regard not well: but they would exclude you, that you might be zealous for them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:18",
      "text": "But be zealous for that which is good in a good thing always: and not only when I am present with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:19",
      "text": "My little children, of whom I am in labour again, until Christ be formed in you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:20",
      "text": "And I would willingly be present with you now and change my voice: because I am ashamed for you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:21",
      "text": "Tell me, you that desire to be under the law, have you not read the law?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:22",
      "text": "For it is written that Abraham had two sons: the one by a bondwoman and the other by a free woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:23",
      "text": "But he who was of the bondwoman was born according to the flesh: but he of the free woman was by promise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:24",
      "text": "Which things are said by an allegory. For these are the two testaments. The one from Mount Sina, engendering unto bondage, which is Agar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:25",
      "text": "For Sina is a mountain in Arabia, which hath affinity to that Jerusalem which now is: and is in bondage with her children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:26",
      "text": "But that Jerusalem which is above is free: which is our mother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:27",
      "text": "For it is written: Rejoice, thou barren, that bearest not: break forth and cry thou that travailest not: for many are the children of the desolate, more than of her that hath a husband.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:28",
      "text": "Now we, brethren, as Isaac was, are the children of promise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:29",
      "text": "But as then he that was born according to the flesh persecuted him that was after the spirit: so also it is now.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:30",
      "text": "But what saith the scripture? Cast out the bondwoman and her son: for the son of the bondwoman shall not be heir with the son of the free woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.4.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 4:31",
      "text": "So then, brethren, we are not the children of the bondwoman but of the free: by the freedom wherewith Christ has made us free.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
